Talks between Japanese and US officials have begun to resume US beef shipments to Japan, the top export market.
Japan, the largest importer of US beef, had halted imports due to mad cow disease fears.
Japan initially required testing of all US beef, but later exempted cows aged 20 months or younger.
The EU may lift embargoes on British beef due to a significant decrease in mad cow cases.
Cases of variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob Disease (vCJD) continue to be reported, highlighting the risks associated with mad cow disease.
